   George Burns, a pioneer in industrial
news photography and one of the combat photographers to shoot the
raising of the American flag on Iwo Jima during World War II, died
Saturday. He was 71.
   In 1939, General Electric Corp., which started the first news
bureau in American industry, hired Burns to oversee it.
