<TEXT>
   Laurence Sickman, former director of the
Nelson Art Gallery in Kansas City and an internationally known
authority on Chinese art, died Saturday at age 81.
   Sickman graduated from Harvard University in 1930 and began
working as an agent for art purchases in China in 1931, two years
before the museum opened. In 1935 he became its first curator of
Oriental art. He retired in 1977.
