   Hogan's works were shown at such galleries as the Whitney Museum
of American Art, the Guggenhem Museum and the Los Angeles County
Museum of Art.
   He studied art at California State University at North Ridge.
His disease first appeared when he was 5 years old, and he used a
wheelchair from the age of 10, when he was given only a few years
to live.
