<HEAD>U.S. Dollar Little Changed, Stock Prices Show Moderate Advance</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar opened slightly lower against the
Japanese yen in early trading in Tokyo Monday while stock prices
showed a moderate advance.
   The dollar opened at 124.73 yen, down 0.15 yen from Friday's
close of 124.88.
   An exchange dealer at a major commercial bank in Tokyo said
there ``will be no major movements'' following a string of national
holidays in Japan last week.
   ``A wait-and-see position will be taken during the day'' by the
many market participants, he added, speaking on condition of
anonymity.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which lost 46.62 points during last Saturday's
half-day session, regained 49.22 points, or 0.17 percent, in the
first 15 minutes of trading and moved to 27,487.77.
